chunk_content: If possible, a unique identifier should be assigned to program participants or names can be collected to track individual participation in the prevention interventions/sites. Site (facility and community) level system should maintain accurate registers for each individual priority population and sum these individual populations when reporting this indicator. How to review for Data should be reviewed regularly for the purposes of program management, to monitor progress data quality: towards achieving targets, and to identify and correct any data quality issues. Testing services disaggregates should not exceed the numerator. How to calculate Sum across both reporting periods; de-duplicating unique individuals already reached and reported in annual total: Q1-Q2 of the same fiscal year in Q4 reporting.
